      • cacheAckIntervalMillis

        public PublishConfiguration.Builder cacheAckIntervalMillis(long cacheAckIntervalMillis)
                                                    throws EventHubClientException.InvalidConfigurationException
        The cache interval dictates how long Event Hub will wait and collect acks before sending to the client Overriding this interval is useful in controlling how often acks are returned to the client
        Parameters:
        cacheAckIntervalMillis - The allowable range is between 100ms to 1 sec with the default being 500ms. The unit is milliseconds
        Returns:
        Builder
        Throws:
        EventHubClientException.InvalidConfigurationException - Thrown if the interval is not within allowable range
